The paper discusses sparse learning techniques and safe screening, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization. The focus is on Lasso, a popular method for feature selection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since these fields often deal with high-dimensional data and optimization problems. The paper also includes experimental results, which suggest that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
